    • Method Detail

      • canBeAssignedToSpecial

        public boolean canBeAssignedToSpecial(Type other)
        Determines whether this type can be assigned to a given type, by assuming that primitive types can only be assigned to the same, identical, primitive type. Moreover, it assumes that void is a subtype of void.
        Overrides:
        canBeAssignedToSpecial in class Type
        Parameters:
        other - what this type should be assigned to
        Returns:
        true if this type is the same as other, false otherwise

      • isOpen

        public boolean isOpen()
        Determines if this type is open, that is, it is a class type whose code cannot be accessed, or can reach an open type.
        Returns:
        false

      • JB_if_cmpeq

        public void JB_if_cmpeq(org.apache.bcel.generic.InstructionList il,
                        org.apache.bcel.generic.InstructionHandle yes)
        Adds to il the Java bytecodes that go to yes if the the top two elements of the stack are equal. In this case, it adds an if_icmpeq Java bytecode, since Booleans are considered integers in the Java bytecode.
        Specified by:
        JB_if_cmpeq in class ComparableType
        Parameters:
        il - the list of instructions that must be expanded
        yes - to place where to jump

        Adds to il the Java bytecodes that go to yes if the the top two elements of the stack are not equal. In this case, it adds an if_icmpne Java bytecode, since Booleans are considered integers in the Java bytecode.
